result.execSummary:
The defendant James A Warriner was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Maintain Drug Trafficking Place [Modifiers: Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.42(1).
  • Manufacture/Deliver THC (<=200g), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(h)1.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
10:04 a.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Jeanne Zamzow.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Court recites agreement - defendant will plea to count 1 & 4 on 2015CF95 as time served and counts 4,5 & 7 on 2015CF122, with probation.  State concurs.  Atty Zamzow concurs.  Defendant concurs.  DA confirms compliance with victim witness rights.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty and as repeater on 2015CF95.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.  (If felony) Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions.

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on counts 1 & 4 on 2015CF95, striking the second subsequent repeater, striking both the repeaters on count 4 and orders counts 2 & 3 be dismissed and read-in.  Court finds the defendant guilty on counts 4,5 & 7 on 2015CF122 as charged and orders counts 1,2,3 & 6 be dismissed and read-in.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  Sentencing statement by DA.  Sentencing statement by Atty Zamzow.  No statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:

2015CF95 (Counts 1 & 4 - EACH)

-Count 1-12 months county jail with 301 days sentence credit.  With huber and to commence within 60 days.
-Count 4-12 months county jail with 301 days sentence credit.  With huber and to commence within 60 days.
-Court costs.
-Defendant is to submit a DNA Sample.

2015CF122 (Counts 4,5 & 7)

-Count 4-SWD, and places the defendant on probation for 5 years.
-Count 5-1 year of Initial Confinement and 1 year of Extended Supervision, stayed and places the defendant on probation for 5 years. (prison sentence is consecutive to any other sentence) 
-Count 7-1 year of Initial Confinement and 1 year of Extended Supervision, stayed and places the defendant on probation for 5 years.  (prison sentence is consecutive to any other sentence)

CONDITIONS:  (EACH COUNT)

-Court costs.
-Defendant is to maintain absolute sobriety - not to possess or consume any alcohol, illegal drugs or prescription drugs without a valid prescription.
-Defendant is to abide by all rules and recommendations of the supervising agent including any counseling and/or treatment as recommended.
-No Contact with JLR or the family members.
-Defendant is to submit a DNA Sample.

-Court finds the defendant not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration program and not eligible for the Substance Abuse program.

Court orders the cash bonds on file be applied to the court costs first on count 1 then on count 4 on 2015CF95, no matter what case the bond is posted on.

Court adjourned at 10:29 a.m.



NOTE:  Spoke with judge re: sentences imposed on 2015CF95 - sentences were meant to be TIME SERVED, so they are to be concurrent.
